Introduction
This Terms & Privacy Policy governs the manner in which Word Block (hereafter also referred to as “we” and “us”) collects, uses, maintains and discloses information collected
from users (each, a “User”) of the Word Block mobile application and its related software platform and tools, and Word Block’s social media accounts, including at Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, and Twitter (hereinafter, collectively referred to as the “Word Block Service”). By accessing the Word Block Service, you acknowledge and agree to this Privacy Policy of the Word Block Service
located at https://sites.google.com/view/wordblockpolicy2019/home
PLEASE READ THIS PRIVACY POLICY CAREFULLY. BY USING THE WORD BLOCK MOBILE APPLICATION (INCLUDING, WITHOUT LIMITATION, ACCESSING OUR WEBSITE, DOWNLOADING AND/OR USING OUR MOBILE APPLICATION OR REGISTERING AN ACCOUNT WITH US), YOU ACKNOWLEDGE THAT YOU HAVE READ, UNDERSTAND, AGREE AND ACCEPT ALL THE TERMS OF THIS PRIVACY POLICY.
INDIVIDUAL REQUESTS FOR WAIVERS OF THE PRIVACY POLICY WILL NOT BE ACCEPTED. THIS PRIVACY POLICY IS NON-NEGOTIABLE.
BY USING THE APPLICATION, YOU SIGNIFY YOUR ACCEPTANCE OF THIS POLICY. IF YOU DO NOT AGREE TO THIS POLICY, PLEASE DO NOT USE OUR APPLICATION. YOUR CONTINUED USE OF THE WORD BLOCK APPLICATION FOLLOWING THE POSTING OF CHANGES TO THIS POLICY WILL BE DEEMED YOUR ACCEPTANCE OF THOSE CHANGES.
Word Block Information Collection
l Personal Information
1. We may collect your Facebook ID and Facebook Profile information when you log in with your Facebook ID.
2. We may collect personally identifiable information in a variety of ways, including, but not limited to, when Users register an account and make use of the tools, features or resources we make available via the Word Block application. This refers to information about you that can be used to contact or identify you and information on your use of and activities related to the Word Block Service.
l Non-Personal Information
1. We may collect your IP address or other unique identifier (“Device Identifier”) for your computer, mobile or other device used to access the Word Block Service (any, a “Device”). A Device Identifier is a number that is automatically assigned to your Device used to access the Word Block Service, and our system identifies your Device by its Device Identifier. Whenever we associate a Device Identifier with your Personal Information, we will treat it as Personal Information.
2. We and our third-party service providers may use a variety of technologies that automatically (or passively) collect certain information whenever you visit or interact with the Word Block Service (“Usage Information”). This Usage Information may include mobile device that you are using, the URL that referred you to the Word Block Service, all of the areas within Word Block Service - that you visit, and the time of day, among other information. We may use Usage Information for various reasons, including enhancing or otherwise improving the Word Block Service.
3. In addition, general location information and precise geo-location information may be collected under your consent. We collect this information for various purposes – including, sending notifications, to provide you with customer support, to send you promotions and offers, to enhance the Word Block Service, and for our internal business purposes.
4. We may also have features that allow you to share this information with other people (such as your family, friends or colleagues) if you choose.
Responding to Do Not Track Signals
For Users in California: The Word Block Application is not presently configured to support Do Not Track (“DNT”) signals from web browsers or mobile devices.
How We Use Your Personal Information？
Personal Information is used to:
1. Provide and improve the Word Block Service and related features and content;
2. Administer your account and your use of the Word Block Application;
3. Enable users to enjoy and easily utilize the mobile application;
4. Better understand your needs and interests;
5. Fulfill requests you may make;
6. Personalize your experience;
7. Send push notification & local notification. You can adjust the notifications you receive by editing your notification settings.
Information is gathered to monitor and analyze use of the Word Block Service, for technical administration, to increase our mobile application’s functionality and user-friendliness, to generate and derive useful data and information concerning the
interests, characteristics of our users, and to verify that the proper information is submitted to fulfill and process your requests.
We may use the email address and other information you provide to respond to User inquiries, questions, and/or other requests.
